This project is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) dashboard app that creates Elasticsearch visualizations using ES|QL and Elastic Charts.

## CRITICAL RULES

1. **NEVER edit, create, or modify any source code files.** This is a tool-based app тАФ interact ONLY through the MCP tools listed below.
2. **ALWAYS read both MCP resources** (`dataviz://guidelines` and `esql://reference`) before creating any charts or dashboards.
3. **ALWAYS call `view_dashboard`** after creating charts to show the live preview.

## What this app CAN do

- Create dashboards with bar, line, area, pie, metric, and heatmap charts
- Execute ES|QL queries against Elasticsearch
- Explore indices and field mappings
- Organize panels into collapsible sections
- Apply custom color palettes to charts and heatmaps
- Apply custom colors to metric panels
- Export dashboards to Kibana as real Lens visualizations
- Import existing Kibana dashboards (ES|QL-based panels only)
- Show interactive dashboard previews inline in chat
- Manage multiple dashboards (create, switch, delete)

## What this app CANNOT do

- Create visualizations from non-ES|QL data sources (index patterns, SQL, etc.)
- Create chart types other than: bar, line, area, pie, metric, heatmap
- Create Kibana alerts, rules, or saved searches
- Modify Kibana settings or spaces
- Create maps or geographic visualizations
- Import dashboards that use index-pattern-based (formBased) queries тАФ only ES|QL panels are supported

## Available MCP tools

**Dashboard management:**
- `create_dashboard` тАФ Create a new dashboard (previous ones are preserved)
- `list_dashboards` тАФ List all saved dashboards
- `switch_dashboard` тАФ Switch to a different dashboard by ID
- `delete_dashboard` тАФ Delete a saved dashboard
- `set_dashboard_title` тАФ Set the active dashboard title
- `get_dashboard` тАФ View current dashboard state
- `clear_dashboard` тАФ Reset the active dashboard

**Data exploration:**
- `run_esql` тАФ Execute ES|QL queries against Elasticsearch
- `list_indices` тАФ Discover available indices
- `get_fields` тАФ Get field mappings for an index

**Visualization creation:**
- `create_chart` тАФ Create bar, line, area, or pie charts. Supports optional `palette` for custom colors.
- `create_metric` тАФ Create metric/KPI panels with optional trend sparklines. Supports `color` for custom background.
- `create_heatmap` тАФ Create heatmap visualizations. Supports optional `colorRamp` for custom gradients.

**Layout & organization:**
- `create_section` тАФ Create collapsible dashboard sections
- `move_panel_to_section` тАФ Assign panels to sections
- `remove_section` тАФ Remove a section
- `remove_chart` тАФ Remove a chart

**Export & import:**
- `export_to_kibana` тАФ Export the active dashboard to Kibana as real Lens visualizations
- `import_from_kibana` тАФ Import an existing Kibana dashboard by ID or URL (ES|QL panels only)
- `view_dashboard` тАФ Display the live dashboard preview inline in the chat

## Available MCP resources

- `dataviz://guidelines` тАФ Data visualization best practices, chart selection, dashboard composition, anti-patterns. **Read this before building dashboards.**
- `esql://reference` тАФ ES|QL language reference with commands, functions, and common query patterns. **Read this when writing ES|QL queries.**

## Workflow

1. Read the dataviz guidelines and ES|QL reference resources
2. Create a new dashboard with `create_dashboard` (or use the active one)
3. Use `list_indices` and `get_fields` to explore available data
4. Use `run_esql` to test queries before creating charts
5. Create visualizations with `create_chart`, `create_metric`, `create_heatmap`
6. Organize with `create_section` and `move_panel_to_section`
7. Call `view_dashboard` to show the interactive preview
8. Export with `export_to_kibana` when ready

## Tips for the AI

- When the user asks for a "themed" dashboard (e.g. "pink themed"), pass matching hex colors via the `palette`, `colorRamp`, and `color` parameters
- Pie charts should have max 6 slices тАФ use `| SORT value DESC | LIMIT 6` in the query
- For time series, always use `BUCKET(@timestamp, interval)` and `SORT` by the time field
- Metric panels benefit from a subtitle for context (e.g. "Last 7 days", "All documents")
- When importing from Kibana, panels using index-pattern queries (not ES|QL) will be skipped тАФ inform the user
